ZCZC OE08
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SATURDAY TO TUESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 262300 UTC
ON SATURDAY EVENING AND SUNDAY AN AREA OF LOW PRESSURE TO
THE E OF ICELAND WILL MOV AWAY NEWARDS. A TRANSITORY
RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE WILL MIGRATE ACROSS THE UK AS
ANOTHER LOW PRESSURE CENTRE 966 DEVELOPS IN MID-ATLANTIC.
HIGH PRESSURE WILL BE CENTRED OVER SIBERIA AND SERN
EUROPE. THROUGH MONDAY DEEP SECONDARY LOW CENTRES WILL
MOV NWARDS TO THE W OF SCOTLAND. THIS DEEP AREA OF LOW
PRESSURE CENTRED NEAR ICELAND WILL CONTINUE THE CYCLONIC
PRESSURE PATTERN ACROSS THE UK THROUGH TUESDAY. ON
SATURDAY EVENING AND SUNDAY WINDS WILL BE STRG AT FIRST
IN FAIR ISLE FAEROES AND SE ICELAND. STRG WINDS WILL
DEVELOP IN ATLANTIC SEA AREAS ON SUNDAY ALTHOUGH WINDS
WILL MOD IN THE FAR N FOR A TIME. WINDS WILL INCREASE
THROUGH MONDAY WITH OCCASIONAL GALES DEVELOPING WIDELY.
THEN ON TUESDAY WINDS WILL DECREASE TO OCNL STRG IN THE
S BUT CONTINUE STRG WITH OCCASIONAL GALES IN THE N
NNNN